title: Summary - Post-Tropical Cyclone Tammy (AT5/AL202023)
author: nhcwebmaster@noaa.gov (NHC Webmaster)
summary:
...TAMMY BECOMES POST-TROPICAL, BUT IT IS STILL PRODUCING HURRICANE-FORCE WINDS... ... THIS IS THE LAST ADVISORY...
 As of 5:00 AM AST Thu Oct 26
 the center of Tammy was located near 30.5, -58.4
 with movement N at 12 mph.
 The minimum central pressure was 973 mb
 with maximum sustained winds of about 85 mph.
